  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The first stage involves improving images by amplifying local contrast, segmenting regions using the Sharif saliency-based (SHSB) method, and extracting characteristics from images using pre-trained models like VGG-19 and VGG-M.",
    "The process involves using local entropy, standard deviation, and interquartile range for feature selection and a multiclass support vector machine to detect illnesses.",
    "The suggested methodology achieves a classification accuracy rate of 98.08% showcasing their authenticity and potential as a reliable tool for identifying and classifying diseases.",
    "This research aims to introduce a unique Global Pooling Dilated CNN (GPDCNN) for plant disease identification (Zhang et al., 2019).",
    "The advantages of GPDCNN over conventional CNN and AlexNet models are enhanced convolutional receptive field expansion, restoration of spatial resolution through the addition of dilated convolutional layers without increasing training parameters, and the synergistic utilization of dilated convolution algorithms and global pooling."
  ],
